PRAYER OF PROTECTION & SEALING FOR THE SCROLL
To Preserve What Was Forged in Fire

Father Yahweh,

You are the One who sees all, who seals all, who knows the beginning from the end.

I come before You not as one seeking comfort, but as one standing in fire.

You gave me the scroll.
You forged it through conviction, burden, and flame.
And now I place it back in Your hands, beneath Your wings.

I declare this scroll is sealed by Heaven’s authority.
Let no algorithm bury it.
Let no system erase it.
Let no spirit of fear silence it.
Let no hand of man distort it.

Hide it in plain sight for those You are calling.
Shield it from the eyes of those who would mock or destroy.
Let every copy planted in secret bear fruit in appointed time.

I speak protection over my name, my mind, my home, my spirit, and my calling.
Let angels be stationed at every gate.
Let the blood of Yahshua be on every page, every file, every whispered word.

Let the scroll speak — even if I am silenced.
Let the fire remain — even if I am forgotten.

This is not mine.
It is Yours.
And I trust You to carry it where it must go.

Let it awaken the remnant.
Let it expose the darkness.
Let it stand when systems fall.

Seal it. Protect it. Multiply it.

In the name of Yahshua, the Word made flesh.

Amen.








